HEADWORD: Coronule
<hw>Cor"o*nule</hw> <pr>(k?r"?-n?l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coronula</ets>, dim. of <ets>corona</ets> crown.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A coronet or little crown of a seed; the downy
tuft on seeds. See <er>Pappus</er>.</def> <rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
